The paper deals with consensus problems in distributed computing, which is a core topic in the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. The use of vectors and real numbers suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. The mention of synchronous and asynchronous systems, as well as the use of norms as distance metrics, suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) and Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-categories. Finally, the mention of lower bounds and optimization suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
